race.comment: DAMASK ROSE (5) caught the eye in the Bellmaine first-up when flashing late for second. Up to 1400m suits better, and she gets the chance to hold a closer spot in the run this time around. Looks the one to beat off what we saw fresh. PARADISE CITY (4) stormed home in the Tressady at Flemington last week in an impressive performance. She came from off speed last week which is unlike her usual pattern and scratchings may see this run differently. However, what she did last start was superb and if she handles the back-up, she can be going close. BENAGIL (1) resumes. She'll be better over further but her fresh run last time in was very good. BOSSY BENITA (9) was well supported in the Bellmaine and ran well for third. Respecting again.
